[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_mu7u0")
reagent_id = "NaCl"
title = "Sodium chloride"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Formula:[/cell][cell]NaCl[/cell]
[cell]Common name:[/cell][cell]Table salt[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]58.5 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]White solid[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Formation reactions[/b]
2Na + Cl₂ → 2NaCl  
NaOH + HCl → NaCl + H₂O  
Na₂O + 2HCl → 2NaCl + H₂O
[b]Important properties[/b]
• Ionic compound made of sodium and chlorine ions.
• Highly soluble in water.
• Forms crystals with a cubic structure.
[b]Where sodium chloride is found[/b]
• In seawater.
• In rock salt deposits.
• In living organisms.
[b]Uses[/b]
• Food seasoning and preservation.
• Production of chlorine and sodium hydroxide.
• Used for de-icing roads.
[b]Safety[/b]
Safe in normal amounts, but excessive consumption can be harmful to health."
